    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "## Smaller polish items (pick up any time)\n\nAll items are known gaps in the shipped chat; none are blocked on the live-collab track.\n\n- **Swarm-link previews in the Files tab.** `MessageBody` already detects `bzz://` URLs and renders inline, but `FilesTab` only iterates `msg.attachment`. Extend the `files` `useMemo` to also sweep `msg.text` for references and synthesize `AttachedFile` entries.\n- **Search inside messages.** Current search only scans the Files tab.\n- **Profile avatars.** Conversation list and message bubbles use initials today. The public profile already carries an optional image ref -- wire it through.\n- **Message deletion / edit.** No UI, no adapter flow. Feeds are append-only, so \"delete\" means writing a tombstone message.\n- **Message reactions.** Small GSOC payloads keyed by message id.\n\n## Explicit out-of-scope\n\n**Group chat is out of scope for live collab** and needs its own design pass. Don't conflate multi-user document collaboration with group-chat conversations -- the data model and invariants differ.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:28.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:28.000Z"
    }
  },
